(1601, 218, 'new_paragraph_3_new_content', '<a href="http://www3.gov.ab.ca/gs/services/lrs/index.cfm" target="_blank">Land Registration Services </a>\r\nService Alberta is responsible for registering land ownership rights in Alberta. The <em>Land Titles Act </em>provides the legislative framework for the department to register land related documents that both create and terminate legal rights in property.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.servicealberta.ca/foip/">Freedom of Information and Protection of Privacy</a>\r\nThis website provides information to help public bodies comply with Alberta''s <i>Freedom of Information and Protection of Privacy Act </i>(FOIP Act).\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.safetycodes.ab.ca/" target="_blank">Government of Canada</a>\r\nThis is the official website for the Government of Canada.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.safetycodes.ab.ca/" target="_blank">Safety Codes Council</a>\r\nThe Safety Codes Council and its partners manage the safety codes system in Alberta.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.aglc.gov.ab.ca/" target="_blank">Alberta Gaming and Liquor Commission\r\n</a>Government of Alberta agency responsible for <em></em>ensuring that the gaming and liquor activities in Alberta are conducted honestly, openly and with integrity, while maximizing the economic benefits of gaming and liquor activities for Albertans.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.nserc.ca/" target="_blank">NSERC</a>\r\nNSERC''s role is to make investments in people, discovery and innovation for the benefit of all Canadians.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.nrc.ca/" target="_blank">NRC</a>\r\nNRC is a  research organization specializing in scientific and technical research (and offering assistance therein). The NRC is also an industrial research-granting agency (IRAP grants).\r\n\r\n<a title="Productivity Alberta" href="http://www.productivityalberta.ca/">Productivity Alberta</a>\r\n\r\nProductivity Alberta offers the latest in productivity assessment and improvement tools and connects you with resources and services that are specific to your industry. They work with government and associations to provide direction and objective input on policy development.'),
